relevant_communication:
Festival is the strongest component of EXIT platform but it is not the only one. It is followed by strong and numerous social activities, campaigns and projects. There are more than 100 projects of EXIT Foundation, and some of the most important ones are (just to name a few): 
2015-2016 – Team of Exit foundation was successfully leading candidacies of the city of Novi Sad  for European Cultural Capital 2021 and European Youth Capital 2019; 
2013 – Youth Heroes award – giving media attention to the prominent young people in society (scientists, humanitarians, entrepreneurs, etc) in opposition to bad influences for youth that are promoted through reality shows, commercial press, etc; 
2012 – Youth Fair – Exit is organizing regional youth tourism fair in Novi Sad; 
2006-2009 – campaign for EU visa liberalization for citizens of Western Balkans (The EU Commissioner for Enlargement, Mr. Olli Rehn spoke at the discussion stage at EXIT Festival); 
2004-2008 – Campaign against human trafficking conducted together with MTV Foundation (global campaign; 
2002 – Serbia are you ready for the future? – campaign promoting EU values and transition in Serbia after Milosevic’s rule; 
EXIT team is now organizing 5 festivals in 5 countries in Southeast Europe: EXIT Festival (Serbia), Sea Dance festival (Montenegro), Revolution festival (Romania), Sea Star Festival (Croatia) and Festival 84 (Bosnia and Herzegovina). All festivals are supported by local and national Governments of these 5 countries.
